  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reinforcing water education and capacity-building for water security</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water education plays a key role in strengthening capacities, improving water management and access to water in a sustainable manner in the short-, medium- and long-terms. To meet various challenges including the Agenda 2030 for Sustainable Development and the Agenda 2063 for Africa, efforts should continue to improve and update water education and capacity-building at all levels. In this framework, IHP-VIII theme 6 positions water education as a key element to attain water security. Water education has to be interpreted in a broader sense than the teaching of hydrological sciences and related scientific disciplines, aiming at working with tertiary and vocational education, with children and the youth, including informal water education.</narrative>
  </description>
